  <file original="why-scratch-for-learning" source-language="en" datatype="SRT" target-language="ta">
    <body>
      <trans-unit id="1" resname="3afcdbfeb6ecfbdd0ba628696e3cc163">
        <source>Scratch is programming languages used by students of all ages</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="2" resname="247730f9d0d2eaad265a470e32aa0cdf">
        <source>to code their own stories, animations, and games.</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="3" resname="cdee9bf40a070d58d14dfa3bb61e0032">
        <source>Educators around the world are using it in all sorts of ways.</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="4" resname="7693e302dc09b57483d26522ef25feb4">
        <source>So when I think about kids interacting with Scratch</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="5" resname="016ce7cd3f0850d6c33696df9f9440d5">
        <source>It's not only about them learning how to code</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="6" resname="8572f81f02517e0c1f0d9b93e407697a">
        <source>and the logical thinking skills that go into it.</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="7" resname="03a149245ce7dd9921af995e04819f39">
        <source>It's about them finding a different way to share their voice.</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8" resname="0b1f4e58fb49b407070c78baeaacf8ad">
        <source>Children, they live with a lot of stories.</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="9" resname="5878d2cab3c6e53c4a1a9526c3df451d">
        <source>Give them Scratch</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10" resname="a7d6fcfc537b66a63062cd141ac8bd87">
        <source>Those stories and those ideas that they have is what they will start to put down on Scratch</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11" resname="314adc507266cc256fcc9d72d670729d">
        <source>And you see the energy coming.</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="12" resname="2fd7e333d36411b88fb3becbacfa8188">
        <source>I've used Scratch in my fourth grade class.</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="13" resname="824bde2ac5edff64c4ffb1f064b1ee4a">
        <source>The themes were up to them.</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14" resname="ecb3257d21a429f4e49462e8639f1494">
        <source>Some made games, some made animations.</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="15" resname="26101031d5115f57d3e8c34f2ac1f741">
        <source>We've done projects around what the year 2050 might be</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="16" resname="ac435aa88d7932bc7c26dbe0277119a3">
        <source>and what we wanted to see is what really matters to them?</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="17" resname="311a0516b1c6eb11a28e8deaa5c64c78">
        <source>What do they think is important?</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="18" resname="a3575631fc76819748da773b5b0087a4">
        <source>We have a project that's called</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="19" resname="2040af1756f3e6429f9b8abab90fb258">
        <source>butterfly botanical garden,</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="20" resname="691513953ea19e01a0e7881a339ce106">
        <source>it's the life cycle of the butterfly.</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="21" resname="867da7e2af8e6b2f3aa7213a4080edb3">
        <source>and the students make sprite, they draw them and animate them</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="22" resname="a6c1243676462dae35ed0c9122125d4e">
        <source>they make robotics</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="23" resname="6994d1415b92982eb7cf57740b15b949">
        <source>and they create their own butterflies.</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="24" resname="061c16448aee6be07e20ab574ef27ea4">
        <source>There's a number different things that learners are gaining from doing Scratch.</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="25" resname="ea8a5a340cab600d88eea120273c4022">
        <source>It gives them confidence</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="26" resname="944024165d37855a16b48158a491e0a5">
        <source>It helps them take the big problem and break it down into the small parts</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="27" resname="d51c2a7526e97b2e9ba2d86ac075af7c">
        <source>Experiment. Fail. It's all of those great parts of Scratch</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="28" resname="99cd002aedd5014650d2d43ca2967c2a">
        <source>that can be applied to any other challenge that comes their way</source>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="29" resname="662a0b32c5caab5e3b8aa9a3f7bcedfc">
        <source>If you want your student's to express themselves using coding, try Scratch!</source>
      </trans-unit>
